# Project Alpha Charter

**Project**: Alpha  
**Status**: Approved  
**Confidence**: Validated (approved by stakeholders)

---

## Executive Summary

Project Alpha aims to improve customer onboarding experience through streamlined workflows and enhanced user interface design. This charter establishes the foundational scope and objectives for the project.

## Project Scope {#project-scope}

### In Scope
- User interface redesign for onboarding flow
- Backend API optimizations for faster response times
- Integration with existing customer data systems
- Mobile-responsive design implementation

### Out of Scope
- Complete system architecture overhaul
- Third-party service integrations beyond current scope
- Advanced analytics and reporting features

## Success Criteria {#success-criteria}

[[success-metrics]] The project will be considered successful when:

1. **User Experience**: 40% reduction in onboarding completion time
2. **Technical Performance**: 50% improvement in API response times  
3. **Business Impact**: 25% increase in onboarding completion rate
4. **Quality**: Zero critical bugs in production for 30 days post-launch

## Timeline

- **Phase 1**: Requirements and Design (2 weeks)
- **Phase 2**: Development and Testing (6 weeks)  
- **Phase 3**: Deployment and Monitoring (2 weeks)

## Resources

- 2 Frontend Developers
- 1 Backend Developer
- 1 UX Designer
- 1 Product Manager
- 1 QA Engineer

## Risks and Mitigation

- **Risk**: Integration complexity with legacy systems
- **Mitigation**: Early technical spike and proof-of-concept

---

**This charter serves as the foundation for all Project Alpha work.**
